<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Pierre Gasly wrote the tale of the unexpected by winning a topsy-turvy Italian Grand Prix.</p>

<p>The Frenchman emerged from the eventful race that had about every spill and trill motor racing has to offer ‚Äì including a red flag ‚Äì to take the top step of the podium for AlphaTauri.</p>

<p>The Rouen-born driver was dumped by Red Bull last season, his belief shot, but here he pulled off the biggest moment of his career aged 24, hanging on to beat the pursuing McLaren of Carlos Sainz, who drove quite beautifully all afternoon in the fan-free royal park.¬†Lance Stroll, of Racing Point, was third.</p>

<p>Pierre Gasly wrote the tale of the unexpected by winning a topsy-turvy Italian Grand Prix</p>

<p>The Frenchman emerged from the race that had every spill and trill motor racing has to offer</p>

<p>As for pole-man Lewis Hamilton, he was victim of a stop-gap penalty for entering the pit lane when it was closed following Kevin Magnussen's Haas conking down early in the piece.</p>

<p>Soon Charles Leclerc had a major shunt. The Ferrari man lost control at the Parabolica, prompting a 27-minute delay in racing. He walked out unharmed despite hitting the tyre wall hard at one of the sport's fastest corners.</p>

<p>Hamilton's mistake caught up with him at about this point. He learned of his punishment as proceedings were halted.</p>

<p>As for pole-man Lewis Hamilton, he was victim of a stop-gap penalty for entering the pit lane</p>

<p>Lewis Hamilton of Mercedes-AMG Petronas endures a pit-stop penalty at the Italian Grand Prix</p>

<p>The race restarted. Hamilton was leading but peeled in the following lap to swerve the sanction. It plunged him 30sec off the lead. He fought his way up, passing eight cars to finish seventh and also took the fastest lap. He was helped in the championship fight by Max Verstappen, of Red Bull, retiring and the other Mercedes, of Valtteri Bottas, finishing a limp fifth.</p>

<p>Canadian Stroll had begun the restart second to Hamilton but he lost his nerve and ran off, his chance of glory gone.</p>

<p>Gasly, who was third as racing began again on lap 28 of the 53, was up into first place, which he never relinquished, finishing 0.4sec ahead of Sainz. 'I just needed one more lap,' said the Spaniard. That was about right.</p>

<p>Race winner Pierre Gasly of France and Scuderia AlphaTauri celebrates in Parc Ferme</p>

<p>Charles Leclerc had major shunt - the Ferrari man lost control at the Parabolica at Monza</p>

<p>Lando Norris, in the other McLaren, finished fourth.</p>

<p>It was a nightmare for Ferrari. In addition to Leclerc's shunt, Sebastian Vettel retired with a brake fault.</p>

<p>Galsy screamed his delight over the radio and cried.</p>

<p>¬†</p>

<p>¬†</p>

<p>Host commentator</p>

<p>Feel the emotion from <?php echo e('@'); ?>AlphaTauriF1 üòç#ItalianGP üáÆüáπ #F1 pic.twitter.com/Vqq6ZidhZk</p>

<p>Alright, who had this guy down to win. üëèüëèWhat a day for <?php echo e('@'); ?>PierreGASLY, <?php echo e('@'); ?>AlphaTauriF1 and F1. pic.twitter.com/L9op7BMge5</p>

<p>'I've been through so many things in the last 18 months and it's better than anything I expected. We focused day-by-day, they gave me my first podium in F1 in Brazil last year and now they've given me my first win. I don't know what to say, it's unbelievable.¬†</p>

<p>'I'm not someone that gives up. I've always had to fight for everything I've wanted in life and that's still the case. My drive to be better and stronger is still so strong. I knew if Sainz got past me I would have been so sad. I literally gave everything I had. The last five laps were so difficult.</p>

<p>'I almost shanked it like five times it was so hard but we got the win and it's amazing. Most of the team is Italian and we are in Italy, I know it's going to be a great time tonight.'</p>

<p>Alpha Tauri team principal Franz Tost hopes Gasly will stay with the team 'for a very long time' and has spoken glowingly about the young Frenchman since his return from Red Bull.</p>

<p>No celebrations for the chief, he's off to a meeting!</p>

<p>Respect ü§ù<?php echo e('@'); ?>LewisHamilton x <?php echo e('@'); ?>PierreGASLY #SkyF1 | #F1 | #ItalianGP üáÆüáπ pic.twitter.com/1d7t2BOy5L</p>

<p>'Firstly I need to say a huge congratulations to Piere. Fantastic result for him. I've seen what he's been through. Dropped from a top team, then beats the top team.</p>

<p>'My race wasn't meant to be today. It was a bit unfortunate. What doesn't kill you makes you stronger. It was a long pit stop! But once I finally caught everybody I enjoyed that battle, Yeah, onto the next one.'¬†</p>

<p>[Interview pauses as Hamilton hugs Pierre Gasly]</p>

<p>'We didn't do a great job with the pit stop. I honestly didn't see those boards but I take responsibility for that. To get 7th and fastest lap is a positive, I will definitely take it. Max didn't score any points, so not a huge loss today.'</p>

<p>The French national anthem is being played out for the race winner, who stands atop the podium with Sainz and Stroll either side of him. The Italian national anthem rings out after Alpha Tauri's win.</p>

<p>Gasly is handed his winner's trophy, while the Alpha Tauri team manager collects a prize for the team-s huge win today.¬†</p>

<p>The champagne is out and the young drivers bask in the glory of their unexpected success, with red, white and green confetti flowing on stage.¬†</p>

<p>'Honestly it's unbelievable I'm not realising what's happening right now. It was such a crazy race.</p>

<p>'We capitalized on the red flag. We had a quick car behind us. I have been through so much in the last 18 months. My first win in Formula One with Monza, it's crazy. I've got no words.</p>

<p>'This team have done so much for me in F1. It's crazy, honestly, I am so happy, I can't thank them enough. It's a power-sensitive track and we beat Mercedes, Red Bull, Renault.</p>

<p>'I never expected it would happen to us but we kept focusing on ourselves since last yeaer, improving step-by-step. I am just so happy.'¬†</p>

<p>'It's incredible that I'm halfway disappointed with P2. I never thought we'd have a chance to win the race today.</p>

<p>'I think I would hav e got P2 behind Lewis if the race continued normally. Very happy with P2 we have been super quick all week and I felt I could dominate the midfield today. We need to be proud of the pace of the car.¬†</p>

<p>'It's been a couple years since I stood on a podium. Feels good to be back. It was a crazy race.</p>

<p>'I'm so happy for Pierre. He stayed consistent all the way throughout the race. It's a bit of a bummer cos it felt like mine to lose but I had a tonne of wheel spin and had a bad restart. I feel the win slipped away from us today but we'll take third place.'¬†</p>

